try to figure out what&#39;s going on using your own faculties of logic and reason.</p><p> But even though I can&#39;t be your single perfect information source, I <em>can</em> try to help you hone your skepticism and recognize when the narrative you&#39;re being fed doesn&#39;t hold up. Last September, I wrote a post about how to spot misleading viral charts: </p><div class="digest-post-embed" data-attrs="{&quot;nodeId&quot;:&quot;0219015e-e8a4-4210-b0fa-7187f3d368ac&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&#8220;The art of any propagandist and agitator consists in his ability to find the best means of influencing any given audience, by presenting a definite truth, in such a way as to make it most convincing, most easy to digest, most graphic, and most strongly impressive.&#8221; &#8212; Lenin&quot;,&quot;size&quot;:&quot;sm&quot;,&quot;isEditorNode&quot;:true,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;How not to be fooled by viral charts&quot;,&quot;publishedBylines&quot;:[{&quot;id&quot;:8243895,&quot;name&quot;:&quot;Noah Smith&quot;,&quot;bio&quot;:&quot;Econ blogger&quot;,&quot;photo_url&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/89fd964a-586f-461a-9f5a-ea4587d45728_397x441.png&quot;,&quot;is_guest&quot;:false,&quot;bestseller_tier&quot;:10000}],&quot;post_date&quot;:&quot;2023-09-13T01:20:51.010Z&quot;,&quot;cover_image&quot;:&quot;https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Ff9b39106-a033-4d58-9a83-ad16b92bcd89_618x620.jpeg&quot;,&quot;cover_image_alt&quot;:null,&quot;canonical_url&quot;:&quot;https://www.noahpinion.blog/p/how-not-to-be-fooled-by-viral-charts&quot;,&quot;section_name&quot;:null,&quot;id&quot;:136955075,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;newsletter&quot;,&quot;reaction_count&quot;:339,&quot;comment_count&quot;:91,&quot;publication_name&quot;:&quot;Noahpinion&quot;,&quot;publication_logo_url&quot;:&quot;https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fbucketeer-e05bbc84-baa3-437e-9518-adb32be77984.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F04281755-2cd6-42e5-a496-e69153abebb2_281x281.png&quot;,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:false}"></div><p>在我给出的示例中 - 其中包括我在彭博日期张贴的图表！ — the data in the chart was either incorrect, or had been presented in a misleading way. But there are also plenty of charts where the underlying data is (probably) solid, and where the presentation of the data isn&#39;t obviously <em>bad</em> , but where the narrative that people attach to the chart isn&#39;t the story the data is really telling 。</p><p> That&#39;s the subject of Part 2 of my guide to How Not to Be Fooled by Viral Charts. I&#39;m going to illustrate what I mean by examining four charts that were very popular and influential in the economic debates of the late 2010s:</p><ol><li><p> The American Enterprise Institute&#39;s “chart of the century”</p></li><li><p> The Economic Policy Institute&#39;s “productivity vs. pay” chart</p></li><li><p> Lakner &amp; Milanovic&#39;s “elephant graph”</p></li><li><p> Lee Drutman&#39;s “political compass” chart</p></li></ol><p> But first, just a quick example of what I&#39;m talking about. The other day, Taylor Nicole Rogers and Eva Xiao wrote <a href="https://www.ft.com/content/f0e38c4d-e875-406d-a61b-78cb7c79a4eb">a story in the Financial Times</a> about how immigrants are helping to sustain the US labor force in the face of the baby boom retirement. They illustrated this with a chart: </p><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><a class="image-link is-viewable-img image2" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F9da4c87d-7692-4a0f-a501-64b09bb5c2e0_815x733.jpeg" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F9da4c87d-7692-4a0f-a501-64b09bb5c2e0_815x733.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F9da4c87d-7692-4a0f-a501-64b09bb5c2e0_815x733.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F9da4c87d-7692-4a0f-a501-64b09bb5c2e0_815x733.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F9da4c87d-7692-4a0f-a501-64b09bb5c2e0_815x733.jpeg 1456w" sizes="100vw"><img src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F9da4c87d-7692-4a0f-a501-64b09bb5c2e0_815x733.jpeg" width="815" height="733" data-attrs="{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/9da4c87d-7692-4a0f-a501-64b09bb5c2e0_815x733.jpeg&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:733,&quot;width&quot;:815,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:null,&quot;bytes&quot;:81169,&quot;alt&quot;:null,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/jpeg&quot;,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:false,&quot;topImage&quot;:false,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:null}" class="sizing-normal" alt="" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F9da4c87d-7692-4a0f-a501-64b09bb5c2e0_815x733.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fim